-- 
Ghana Plans 13 Additional Oil Shipments By Aug. 1, GNPC Says

-- B y   J a s o n   M c L u r e
-- 
2011-03-14T13:43:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/ghana-plans-13-additional-oil-shipments-by-aug-1-gnpc-says.html
Ghana  will ship 13 additional
cargoes of crude from its offshore Jubilee field by Aug. 1,
according to a loading schedule released by the state-owned
Ghana National Petroleum Corp.  Four shipments totaling 3.6 million barrels have been
transported since the offshore field began test production in
November, according to a statement e-mailed today. Major
partners in the field include  Tullow Oil Plc (TLW) ,  Anadarko Petroleum
Corp. (APC) , Kosmos Energy Ltd. and Ghana National.  Tullow is scheduled to ship five cargoes of 950,000 barrels
each during the period. Scheduled shipping dates are March 19,
April 7, June 1, June 29 and July 24.  Anadarko is scheduled to ship three cargos of 950,000
barrels each during the period. Planned shipping dates are May
6, June 11, and July 16.  Ghana National will lift three shipments of 950,000 barrels
on May 20, July 7 and August 1.  Kosmos, which has planned an initial public offering to
raise as much as $500 million on the New York Stock Exchange, is
slated to ship two cargoes totaling 1.9 million barrels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason McLure in Accra at 
 jmclure@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 